                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.0023/1–247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 2, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. Dept press release note re Dairen (Moscow’s 3 Jan 2, 3 pm) will be in form
                    sent Soviet authorities with added comment similar <pb facs="0492" n="482"
                        xml:id="pg_482"/> note sent Chinese FonOff. If your note still undelivered
                    request you make alteration recommended by Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
